---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---
<Layout
  title="Kitchen Renovations Canberra &amp; the ACT | Service Areas"
  description="Kitchen renovations across Canberra & the ACT — Belconnen, Gungahlin, Tuggeranong, Woden, Dickson plus Queanbeyan, Weston Creek, Molonglo and Kingston. Custom cabinetry, stone benchtops, full renovations. ACT-licensed."
  canonical="https://kitchenrenovationscanberra.com.au/canberra-region/"
>
  <Fragment slot="head">
  </Fragment>

  <section class="hero">
    <div class="hero-inner">
      <span class="hero-eyebrow">Canberra &amp; the ACT &middot; full coverage</span>
      <h1>Kitchen renovations across <span class="accent">Canberra &amp; the ACT</span>.</h1>
      <p class="hero-sub">
        From the established 1970s&ndash;80s districts to the newer northern
        suburbs and the premium inner-north &mdash; and into Queanbeyan and the
        surrounding region. One ACT-licensed team for full renovations, custom
        cabinetry, stone benchtops, design and makeovers, wherever you are in
        the ACT.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a class="ph-cta btn btn-primary" href="/quote/" aria-label="Call us"><span aria-hidden="true">&#9742;</span> <span class="ph-text">Tap to call</span></a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Get a free quote</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <span class="section-eyebrow">Full coverage</span>
      <h2>Suburbs &amp; districts we cover.</h2>
      <div class="divider"></div>
      <div style="max-width: 65rem;">
        <h3>Featured district pages.</h3>
        <p>Each with local context &mdash; housing era, the typical renovation brief, and what to watch for.</p>
        <div class="areas-grid" style="margin: 1.5rem 0 2.5rem 0;">
          <a class="area-pill" href="/belconnen/">Belconnen</a>
          <a class="area-pill" href="/gungahlin/">Gungahlin</a>
          <a class="area-pill" href="/tuggeranong/">Tuggeranong</a>
          <a class="area-pill" href="/woden/">Woden</a>
          <a class="area-pill" href="/dickson/">Dickson</a>
        </div>

        <h3>Other Canberra &amp; region areas we cover.</h3>
        <div class="areas-grid" style="margin: 1.5rem 0 2.5rem 0;">
          <span class="area-pill area-pill-static">Queanbeyan</span>
          <span class="area-pill area-pill-static">Weston Creek</span>
          <span class="area-pill area-pill-static">Molonglo Valley</span>
          <span class="area-pill area-pill-static">Kingston</span>
          <span class="area-pill area-pill-static">Civic</span>
          <span class="area-pill area-pill-static">Ainslie</span>
          <span class="area-pill area-pill-static">Lyneham</span>
          <span class="area-pill area-pill-static">Curtin</span>
          <span class="area-pill area-pill-static">Garran</span>
          <span class="area-pill area-pill-static">Kambah</span>
          <span class="area-pill area-pill-static">Wanniassa</span>
          <span class="area-pill area-pill-static">Kaleen</span>
          <span class="area-pill area-pill-static">Bruce</span>
          <span class="area-pill area-pill-static">Harrison</span>
          <span class="area-pill area-pill-static">Casey</span>
          <span class="area-pill area-pill-static">Forde</span>
          <span class="area-pill area-pill-static">Phillip</span>
          <span class="area-pill area-pill-static">Mawson</span>
        </div>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">A district-by-district read on Canberra kitchens.</h3>
        <p>
          <strong>Belconnen &amp; Tuggeranong</strong> &mdash; Canberra&rsquo;s big
          1970s&ndash;90s family districts, where the original closed-off kitchen
          is overdue for a full renovation and an open-plan reconfiguration.
          See <a href="/belconnen/">Belconnen</a> and
          <a href="/tuggeranong/">Tuggeranong</a>.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>Gungahlin</strong> &mdash; the newer north, where builder-grade
          project-home kitchens are upgraded to custom cabinetry, stone benchtops
          and butler&rsquo;s pantries by households with the budget to do it well.
          See <a href="/gungahlin/">Gungahlin</a>.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>Woden Valley</strong> &mdash; established, central, renovated to
          keep. Premium, design-led kitchens, with careful pre-1980 asbestos
          handling given the area&rsquo;s Mr Fluffy history.
          See <a href="/woden/">Woden</a>.
        </p>
        <p>
          <strong>Dickson &amp; the inner-north</strong> &mdash; period and
          mid-century character homes wanting heritage-sympathetic, high-end
          kitchens built to modern standards underneath.
          See <a href="/dickson/">Dickson</a>.
        </p>

        <h3 style="margin-top: 2rem;">What every Canberra kitchen renovation should get right.</h3>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>The right licences.</strong> Building, plumbing and electrical work to the <strong>Construction Occupations (Licensing) Act 2004</strong> via Access Canberra, with ACTPLA approval where structure or footprint changes.</li>
          <li><strong>Compliant standards.</strong> Plumbing to AS/NZS 3500, electrical to AS/NZS 3000, wet-area waterproofing to AS 3740 where it adjoins.</li>
          <li><strong>Legal, safe stone.</strong> Only compliant benchtop materials after the 1 July 2024 engineered-stone silica ban &mdash; natural stone, porcelain, or low-silica engineered stone.</li>
          <li><strong>Asbestos handled, not hidden.</strong> In pre-1985 homes (and the ACT&rsquo;s Mr Fluffy loose-fill legacy, 1968&ndash;1980) suspect materials are tested and removed by licensed contractors before demolition.</li>
          <li><strong>One fixed price.</strong> An itemised written quote and program before work starts &mdash; no surprises.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section-alt">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <span class="section-eyebrow">All five services</span>
      <h2>What we do.</h2>
      <div class="svc-grid">
        <a class="svc-card" href="/services/full-kitchen-renovation/"><h3>Full kitchen renovation</h3><p>Design to fit-off by one team. Mid-range $27.5K&ndash;$50K typical.</p><span class="svc-link">See &rarr;</span></a>
        <a class="svc-card" href="/services/custom-cabinetry/"><h3>Custom cabinetry</h3><p>Australian-made, soft-close, built to your exact layout.</p><span class="svc-link">See &rarr;</span></a>
        <a class="svc-card" href="/services/benchtops/"><h3>Stone &amp; laminate benchtops</h3><p>Compliant stone, porcelain &amp; laminate. $550&ndash;$3,000 per m&sup2;.</p><span class="svc-link">See &rarr;</span></a>
        <a class="svc-card" href="/services/kitchen-design/"><h3>Kitchen design</h3><p>3D design, layout, storage &amp; lighting planned before the build.</p><span class="svc-link">See &rarr;</span></a>
        <a class="svc-card" href="/services/kitchen-makeovers/"><h3>Budget makeovers</h3><p>Doors, benchtop &amp; handles refresh. From around $8,800.</p><span class="svc-link">See &rarr;</span></a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="section-inner">
      <div class="cta-block">
        <h2>Free kitchen quote anywhere in Canberra &amp; the ACT.</h2>
        <p>Belconnen to the inner-north, Gungahlin to Queanbeyan. Free in-home measure most weeks.</p>
        <div class="hero-actions" style="justify-content:center;">
          <a class="ph-cta btn btn-primary" href="/quote/" aria-label="Call us"><span aria-hidden="true">&#9742;</span> <span class="ph-text">Tap to call</span></a>
          <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="/quote/">Get a free quote</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
